==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: goldfields
<hw>goldfields</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small slender woolly annual
(<spn>Lasthenia chrysostoma</spn>) with very narrow opposite leaves and
branches bearing solitary golden-yellow flower heads; it grows from
Southwestern Oregon to Baja California and Arizona; -- it is often
cultivated.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> <spn>Lasthenia chrysostoma</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Goldfinch</ent>⟦br⟧
